<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/148401AHQDJPRRQDPKTJSVKMQLBTGVMGT>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Birdy";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Freedom Has Wings… A powerful contemporary dance rooted in history, resistance, and flight.</h1><span><br/></span>Birdy is Hung Dance’s exhilarating call to the wild, where creatures of a feather move together and fracture apart. Featuring the Ling Zi headpiece, pheasant tail feathers from traditional Chinese opera symbolizing a warrior’s power, the work conjures a magpie-inspired vision, flashing moments of freedom against the cage of history. Drawing from martial arts, Peking opera, and cultural symbolism, the choreography transforms Taiwan’s political and historical complexity into a vivid contemporary dance language. Shifting from tenderness to ferocity, long feathers extend the body, at times weapon, at times whisper, while dancers flock, conform, and resist in a visceral meditation on identity, control, and the human desire for freedom.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-13T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
