<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/165601ATDGBBLSKBVNBVPSRGPVNPVDQSD>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Completely Creedence Band";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Get ready for a night of classic rock as Completely Creedence Band brings the music of Creedence Clearwater Revival to life.</h1><span><br/></span>Known for their high-energy performances and authentic sound, the band delivers all the CCR favourites audiences know and love - including Proud Mary, Bad Moon Rising, Fortunate Son, and Have You Ever Seen the Rain.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Fronted by Jamie Robertson, whose vocals capture the unmistakable tone and spirit of John Fogerty, and backed by a talented lineup of seasoned musicians - Murray Atkinson (lead guitar), Lance Lapointe (bass), and Grant Baird (drums) - Completely Creedence delivers tight musicianship, strong harmonies, and the timeless groove that defined a generation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Completely Creedence recreates the sound and feel of CCR with passion, precision, and heart. Their performances are more than a tribute - they’re an experience that transports audiences back to the golden era of rock. With over a decade of performing together, the band has built a reputation for engaging live shows that have audiences singing along, clapping, and on their feet. Whether you’re a lifelong fan or discovering the music for the first time, this is a show that celebrates the songs, the energy, and the legacy of one of rock’s most iconic bands.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-30T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
