<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/67601AVHPCSTMMBKTGKLCGLQQCGMMBVSK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Dungeons & Dragons Camp (13-15)";
  schema:description """
	Put more adventure in your summer – put on your Cap of Thinking, cast Imagination and join the party! No experience necessary! Our experienced instructors will start each session off with a little creativity, including character creation, painting a miniature, creating one of the many monsters from the lore, and developing the world in which your adventure takes place. Our professional Dungeon Masters will guide you through two hours of game play every day, encouraging cooperation, respect, creativity, storytelling, and inspiring players to take courageous steps to complete their campaign! Sessions are capped at 6 players per table for each age group to ensure the most on-on-one time possible. Two age groups available – 8-12 and 13-15. All students will take home their own set of dice, a completed character, and their own hand-painted miniature. When registering your child, please indicate which child will be attending in the order notes. Please note that we have updated requirements for registration, behaviour policy, accessibility limitations, and student waivers. 
""";
