<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/33402AVMTCTQMGMCTBTVQVGGJBTJNQLDN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Eggs, Flour, and Love";
  schema:description """
	<h1> Eggs, Flour, and Love and 101 Dalmatians KIDS</h1><span><br/></span>EGGS, FLOUR, AND LOVE<span><br/></span>CSOPA’s JR Devised Theatre class (ages 8-11) presents Eggs, Flour, and Love! This show was written entirely by the students of the JR Devised class! In the once homely Noodleton Noodlery, cousins Mac and Cap have inherited the family business, and turned their grandparents homely restaurant into a high-end 5 star establishment. But all is not as perfect as the ratings would imply. Behind the glitz and glamor, Mac and Cap have forgotten the true values of the Noodleton Noodlery in their quest for stardom. The once close-knit Noodleton family has fractured. Meanwhile, on the eve of the most important and celebrity-stacked dinner the restaurant has ever seen, the staff of this once loving family are about to hit their limit with this new unattainable standard. Can the Noodleton family cut through all the ostentatiousness, and remember the value of good ol’ eggs, flour, and love?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>101 DALMATIANS KIDS<span><br/></span>CSOPA’s Intermediate Musical Theatre class (ages 11-13) brings a furry cast of characters to life in 101 Dalmatians KIDS! Pet owners, Roger and Anita, live happily in London with their Dalmatians, Pongo and Perdita, stalwart dogs devoted to raising their puppies. Everything is quiet until Anita’s former classmate, the monstrous Cruella De Vil, plots to steal the puppies for her new fur coat. The Dalmatians rally all the dogs of London for a daring rescue of the puppies from Cruella and her bumbling henchmen.
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-05-22T16:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/d35ab9a4-2748-44b5-9abd-f576f30df2db.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/location/4201ASVGBHHRTVLQBSRVKDQCKNHHDCTSJ>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36867975;
  schema:keywords "Festival";
  schema:duration "PT105M";
  schema:endDate "2025-05-22T18:15:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36867975 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "19.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/34002AJRJRNJJNDLJCMCCPHKBSPHKJKKN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Eggs, Flour, and Love";
  schema:description """
	<h1> Eggs, Flour, and Love and 101 Dalmatians KIDS</h1><span><br/></span>EGGS, FLOUR, AND LOVE<span><br/></span>CSOPA’s JR Devised Theatre class (ages 8-11) presents Eggs, Flour, and Love! This show was written entirely by the students of the JR Devised class! In the once homely Noodleton Noodlery, cousins Mac and Cap have inherited the family business, and turned their grandparents homely restaurant into a high-end 5 star establishment. But all is not as perfect as the ratings would imply. Behind the glitz and glamor, Mac and Cap have forgotten the true values of the Noodleton Noodlery in their quest for stardom. The once close-knit Noodleton family has fractured. Meanwhile, on the eve of the most important and celebrity-stacked dinner the restaurant has ever seen, the staff of this once loving family are about to hit their limit with this new unattainable standard. Can the Noodleton family cut through all the ostentatiousness, and remember the value of good ol’ eggs, flour, and love?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>101 DALMATIANS KIDS<span><br/></span>CSOPA’s Intermediate Musical Theatre class (ages 11-13) brings a furry cast of characters to life in 101 Dalmatians KIDS! Pet owners, Roger and Anita, live happily in London with their Dalmatians, Pongo and Perdita, stalwart dogs devoted to raising their puppies. Everything is quiet until Anita’s former classmate, the monstrous Cruella De Vil, plots to steal the puppies for her new fur coat. The Dalmatians rally all the dogs of London for a daring rescue of the puppies from Cruella and her bumbling henchmen.
""";
