<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/171001APLJSPHTNHJTTCLSMLNGGLBPRMS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Little Women";
  schema:description """
	<h1>A Story of Family, Courage, and the Bonds That Shape Us.</h1><span><br/></span>Celebrate the timeless power of sisterhood in Louisa May Alcott’s Little Women, beautifully reimagined in Lauren M. Gunderson’s luminous adaptation. Set against the backdrop of the Civil War, this heartfelt coming-of-age story follows the four March sisters, bold Jo, devoted Meg, gentle Beth, and ambitious Amy, as they navigate love, loss, family, and the courage it takes to define womanhood on their own terms. As each sister wrestles with her dreams and desires, they are bound together by loyalty, resilience, and an unbreakable bond. Brimming with warmth, wit, and emotional honesty, this radiant production invites audiences to rediscover a beloved classic while celebrating the enduring strength of home, hope, and human connection through a modern, deeply human lens.
""";
  schema:startDate "2027-03-17T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
