<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/26201AGBHCTNMDGTRMRCVQPKJNVHQTBBK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Macbeth";
  schema:description """
	With the highly anticipated directorial return of associate professor Bruce Kirkley, Macbeth, will be performing from March 20 - 29, 2025. This will be the second production of UFV Theatre's 2024-2025 season and in addition to its run at UFV Abbotsford’s Blackbox Theatre, it will also be performed in Chilliwack at the Chilliwack Cultural Centre’s Rotary Theatre.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Presented by the UFV SOCA Acting and Production Classes, Macbeth is a masterwork in tragedy by William Shakespeare, written in 1623. Adapted to be set in a dystopian future, the play follows the rise and fall of a brave general driven to murder and madness by his ambition and a prophecy. The play explores themes of power, guilt, and the corrupting influences of unchecked ambition.
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-03-27T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/d586984b-ffda-4578-9528-b58a42190041.jpg>;
