<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/54201ATDGHQSBGRJPLVKLMRQMLSGRSDLV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Shades of Identity";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Los Angeles-based dance company, Bernard Brown/BBMoves, makes its Canadian debut with their breath-taking dance show, Shades of Identity: Stories of Immigration, Liberation and Love. </h1><span><br/></span>Known for their thought-provoking choreography and visceral performances, BBMoves was formed in 2015, inspired by the social justice movements from both past and present. Their founder, activist and choreographer Bernard Brown, uses dance to highlight current cultural themes and as a conduit for marginalized voices. Shades of Identity invites audiences to grapple with poignant themes such as migration, belonging and freedom in a rapidly changing world.
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-10-24T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/44e81637-bf21-445c-802e-d87c32f5b96d.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/location/4201ASVGBHHRTVLQBSRVKDQCKNHHDCTSJ>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868331;
  schema:keywords "Dance";
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2025-10-24T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868331 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "29.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/136601AQRDSQHQHPRPTLHLPPLSTVLQTRL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Silver Screen - Sorrowful Jones";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Get your popcorn ready!</h1><span><br/></span>In an upcoming exhibition, the Chilliwack Museum is chronicling the vibrant history of live theatre and cinema in our community, opening June 2026. Visitors will be invited to engage with meaningful stories, shared knowledge, activities, and preserved artifacts. Through this memorable experience, you'll gain, or reaffirm, an appreciation for the longstanding value of live theatre and cinema, as mediums for storytelling and places for community gathering.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This event will show the first film screened at the Paramount when it opened its doors to the public.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The film will also be shown on the actual Paramount Silver Screen which was brought to The Chilliwack Cultural Centre when the Paramount closed its doors to the public. This event is being held in collaboration with the Chilliwack Museum and is part of their exhibit featuring film and the performing arts in Chilliwack.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-25T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/6967429c-ca3d-43eb-bac9-dae0f3775b89.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/location/4201ASVGBHHRTVLQBSRVKDQCKNHHDCTSJ>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868332;
  schema:keywords "Film";
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-06-25T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868332 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "20.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/43001AKSPRSSKSHNTDHGBHCHQCHRJRSDT>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Simon & Garfunkel";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Experience the Timeless Music of Simon & Garfunkel: A Musical Celebration Featuring Michael Sicoly and Mick Dalla-Vee. </h1><span><br/></span>Fans of the legendary duo Simon & Garfunkel will be transported back in time with \"Simon & Garfunkel: A Musical Celebration,\" an extraordinary live concert event featuring the talents of Michael Sicoly and Mick Dalla-Vee. This 90-minute musical journey will showcase the timeless hits of Paul Simon and Art Garfunkel, delivering an unforgettable experience for music lovers of all ages. Highlights of the concert include iconic classics such as: The Sound of Silence, Mrs Robinson, The Boxer, and a stunning rendition of Bridge Over Troubled Water. In addition to these timeless hits, the show will explore the early influences that shaped the music of Simon & Garfunkel, as well as selections from both Paul Simon and Art Garfunkel’s successful solo careers.
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-05-14T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/2b80bcc0-fc7e-4501-a52c-44df47eb0614.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/location/4201ASVGBHHRTVLQBSRVKDQCKNHHDCTSJ>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868333;
  schema:keywords "Tribute Band";
  schema:duration "PT90M";
  schema:endDate "2025-05-14T21:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868333 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "45.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/111001ANTCDJDHBHGBVLDTVRJMGTJMBPQ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Sketching With Charcoal";
  schema:description """
	Jump into the world of charcoal sketching! This flexible and forgiving medium has been connected with human art for thousands of years. Its versatility allows for a multitude of different looks with one simple stick, perfect for someone looking for a new creative outlet! 
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-01-12T18:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
