<http://www.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/event/97201AMPBGQVTDNKMCRQSQPLRVBSVPHQP>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Wizard of Oz ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Get swept away into another world somewhere over the rainbow with CSOPA’s production of The Wizard of OZ!</h1><span><br/></span>We’re off to see the Wizard! Join CSOPA’s MainStage program for the beloved classic tale of the Wizard of OZ. Follow the yellow brick road in this delightful stage adaptation of L. Frank Baum’s beloved tale, featuring the iconic musical score from the MGM film. A young farm girl, Dorthy Gale, gets swept away into the fantastical world of OZ by a tornado. She journeys along the Yellow Brick Road to the Emerald City to ask the famous wizard of OZ for help in returning home. Along the way, she befriends a Scarecrow, Tin Man, and Cowardly Lion, who are also seeking to have wishes granted. To gain his aid, they must defeat the Wicked Witch of the West! Will Dorthy and her new friends make it to the Wizard and have their wishes granted, Or has what they sought been in them all along?
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-01-15T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/files/b253bfc6-b910-4025-b502-dca91ba3214b.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/chilliwackculturalcentre/location/4201ASVGBHHRTVLQBSRVKDQCKNHHDCTSJ>;
  schema:offers _:1290a8eb9d794355b3e34223272b36868456;
  schema:keywords "Musical Theatre";
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-01-15T20:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

